WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.223 --> 00:00:16.642
{\an8}<i> Peter Irvine. I have your son.</i>

2
00:00:16.725 --> 00:00:18.477
{\an8}If this is a prank call.
I swear to God...

3
00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:19.519
{\an8}<i> It's not a prank.</i>

4
00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:21.271
{\an8}<i>You tell anybody about this.</i>

5
00:00:21.354 --> 00:00:23.607
{\an8}<i>you never find out what
happens to your son.</i>

6
00:00:23.690 --> 00:00:25.317
<i>He just won't ever come home.</i>

7
00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:27.653
<i>You need to get
some cash together.</i>

8
00:00:27.736 --> 00:00:30.113
You had a gambling problem.
I went into business with you.

9
00:00:30.196 --> 00:00:31.406
You're so grateful.
-I <i>am</i> grateful.

10
00:00:31.489 --> 00:00:32.449
There's a trust I manage.

11
00:00:32.532 --> 00:00:33.700
Let's use the funds from there

12
00:00:33.783 --> 00:00:35.160
to replenish
the Philips account.

13
00:00:35.243 --> 00:00:36.662
<i>-Whose trust is it?</i>
-Lia Irvine.

14
00:00:36.745 --> 00:00:38.413
Hey. Col.

15
00:00:38.496 --> 00:00:39.498
Hey.

16
00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:40.582
<i>My sister's unpredictable.</i>

17
00:00:40.665 --> 00:00:41.792
She's sweet and she's fun.

18
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:43.168
<i>and then there's a mess
to clean up.</i>

19
00:00:43.251 --> 00:00:45.420
Brian was. uh.
not born disabled.

20
00:00:45.503 --> 00:00:48.298
There was an accident.
and it was Lia's fault.

21
00:00:48.381 --> 00:00:50.175
He can't communicate with us.
Case.

22
00:00:50.258 --> 00:00:53.428
You're a great mom.
He loves you to pieces.

23
00:00:53.511 --> 00:00:55.222
I'm here to pick up
my son. Milo.

24
00:00:55.305 --> 00:00:56.807
I think
you've got the wrong house.

25
00:00:56.890 --> 00:00:58.183
Oh. uh...

26
00:00:58.266 --> 00:00:59.643
I didn't know
if you'd want to see me.

27
00:00:59.726 --> 00:01:02.271
Must bring up awful memories.

28
00:01:02.354 --> 00:01:04.439
<i>Ana and Carrie were friends.</i>

29
00:01:04.522 --> 00:01:06.566
I do know Carrie Finch.

30
00:01:06.649 --> 00:01:09.194
She wanted to know what
kinds of food Milo likes

31
00:01:09.277 --> 00:01:10.696
and his bedtime routine.

32
00:01:10.779 --> 00:01:13.532
-What happened. Ana?
-She was with someone.

33
00:01:13.615 --> 00:01:16.368
Now I think that
she wanted them to meet Milo.

34
00:01:16.451 --> 00:01:18.203
<i>How well do you remember
the Chicago Marathon?</i>

35
00:01:18.286 --> 00:01:19.496
<i>It was the day that
this man met Milo.</i>

36
00:01:19.579 --> 00:01:20.831
<i>What happened?</i>

37
00:01:20.914 --> 00:01:22.624
Did he do something to Milo?
Did he hurt Milo?

38
00:01:22.707 --> 00:01:24.751
So after you tag
marathon. running.

39
00:01:24.834 --> 00:01:26.420
Chicago. stuff like that.

40
00:01:26.503 --> 00:01:29.089
and then you run
a facial recognition software

41
00:01:29.172 --> 00:01:31.883
for both Milo and Carrie.
then this is what you get.

42
00:01:31.966 --> 00:01:33.302
Who are you?

43
00:01:33.385 --> 00:01:34.636
<i>Local authorities
have reiterated</i>

44
00:01:34.719 --> 00:01:36.555
<i>the importance
of coordinated efforts</i>

45
00:01:36.638 --> 00:01:38.098
<i>and praised volunteers</i>

46
00:01:38.181 --> 00:01:40.684
<i>for their dedication
and cooperation.</i>

47
00:01:40.767 --> 00:01:42.603
<i>If you have any information
that may assist</i>

48
00:01:42.686 --> 00:01:46.648
<i>in locating Milo. please
contact local authorities.</i>

49
00:03:04.726 --> 00:03:07.271
It's open.

50
00:03:07.354 --> 00:03:11.232
Do you want a new one?

51
00:03:15.779 --> 00:03:18.615
I said do you want a new one?

52
00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:21.493
Uh. no.

53
00:03:21.576 --> 00:03:24.371
No. it's. uh... it's good.

54
00:03:26.289 --> 00:03:28.625
8.29.

55
00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.863
I'm tired.

56
00:03:57.946 --> 00:04:00.365
Oh. I know.

57
00:04:00.448 --> 00:04:02.868
I'll get you back to
your bed soon. OK?

58
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:05.787
My real bed or my vacation bed?

59
00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:07.539
Vacation bed.

60
00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:09.583
You like it. right?

61
00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:11.293
Yeah.

62
00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:13.837
We'll get back to
the vacation house real soon.

63
00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:16.506
But first we need to do
one quick thing. OK?

64
00:04:16.589 --> 00:04:19.051
Just you and me.

65
00:04:19.134 --> 00:04:21.303
Why not Carrie?

66
00:04:21.386 --> 00:04:23.388
Remember? I told you?

67
00:04:23.471 --> 00:04:27.100
Carrie has to hide whenever
she can 'cause she's famous.

68
00:04:29.644 --> 00:04:31.897
Are you famous?

69
00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:35.025
No.

70
00:04:35.108 --> 00:04:38.862
Because you can't have
two famous people. Milo.

71
00:04:46.786 --> 00:04:49.330
That would be a problem.

72
00:04:57.714 --> 00:04:59.841
{\an8}I looked at the website
again. Jim.

73
00:04:59.924 --> 00:05:02.052
Yeah.

74
00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:06.098
He'd be with kids
with the same diagnosis.

75
00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:10.018
He'd have his own aide all day.

76
00:05:10.101 --> 00:05:13.021
One person to take him
to the bathroom.

77
00:05:13.104 --> 00:05:14.606
Or help him with his meals.

78
00:05:14.689 --> 00:05:15.983
or...
-Take him to the pool.

79
00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:18.360
Because they have
their own pool.

80
00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:25.951
I hate how much I want it.

81
00:05:26.034 --> 00:05:28.036
I hate thinking about
how much more he could develop

82
00:05:28.119 --> 00:05:31.915
if he just... just had help.

83
00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:35.961
Honey. I want it too.

84
00:05:36.044 --> 00:05:37.713
But they only have one spot.

85
00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:39.756
It's a lottery.

86
00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:42.718
For someone's future.

87
00:05:42.801 --> 00:05:46.471
It's... it's so wrong.

88
00:05:46.554 --> 00:05:48.139
It's so wrong.

89
00:05:54.979 --> 00:05:56.982
You know what I thought of
the other day?

90
00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:59.443
What?

91
00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.820
Sam's never gonna be an asshole.

92
00:06:01.903 --> 00:06:03.905
Of course
he won't be an asshole.

93
00:06:03.988 --> 00:06:05.532
Well. no. no.

94
00:06:05.615 --> 00:06:06.992
OK. just think of all the
assholes in the world. right?

95
00:06:07.075 --> 00:06:09.494
No. like...

96
00:06:09.577 --> 00:06:11.038
just. like. everyday people
you don't want to be around.

97
00:06:11.121 --> 00:06:12.539
Yeah.

98
00:06:12.622 --> 00:06:15.083
-Those assholes...
-Mm-hmm.

99
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:17.002
They have parents.

100
00:06:17.085 --> 00:06:18.462
-Yeah. I know.
-Right?

101
00:06:18.545 --> 00:06:19.880
OK.

102
00:06:19.963 --> 00:06:21.757
And so would you rather
have an asshole like that

103
00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:22.966
as your grown-up kid?

104
00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:24.134
You know. somebody who's married

105
00:06:24.217 --> 00:06:25.636
and has a job
and all that normal stuff?

106
00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:27.679
Or would you rather

107
00:06:27.762 --> 00:06:30.056
have...
-Sam?

108
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:36.938
Yeah. Sam.

109
00:06:39.190 --> 00:06:40.776
Look. I know he's never
gonna live independently.

110
00:06:40.859 --> 00:06:44.529
and maybe he doesn't do math.

111
00:06:44.612 --> 00:06:46.657
but he's never gonna be someone
you don't want to be around.

112
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:47.740
Oh.

113
00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:54.456
And he's always good for a hug.

114
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.750
We're lucky.
-We're lucky.

115
00:07:02.213 --> 00:07:06.927
I'd still do anything
to get him into St. Mark's.

116
00:07:07.010 --> 00:07:08.220
Anything.

117
00:07:08.303 --> 00:07:10.889
Me too.

118
00:07:10.972 --> 00:07:12.474
<i>I'm applying
for a new villain loan.</i>

119
00:07:12.557 --> 00:07:14.935
<i>Go by the name of Vector.</i>

120
00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:16.812
We ran facial recognition
on the guy.

121
00:07:16.895 --> 00:07:18.063
From the marathon?

122
00:07:18.146 --> 00:07:20.148
Yeah.
and we didn't get any hits.

123
00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:21.984
There was a shadow
from the hoodie.

124
00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:23.694
-I'm sorry.
-Yeah.

125
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:26.071
And we don't have. uh.
an ID on the nanny yet.

126
00:07:26.154 --> 00:07:29.950
No ransom demand to work off
of. and we're on day four.

127
00:07:30.033 --> 00:07:31.660
You gonna release
the picture to the public?

128
00:07:31.743 --> 00:07:33.453
We've still got one more
Hail Mary.

129
00:07:33.536 --> 00:07:35.080
After that. I don't know.

130
00:07:35.163 --> 00:07:36.832
I mean. if we put his
picture out there...

131
00:07:36.915 --> 00:07:38.125
Well. then he'll know
you're looking for him.

132
00:07:38.208 --> 00:07:40.293
Yeah. exactly.

133
00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:47.593
You think he could be violent?

134
00:07:47.676 --> 00:07:49.928
Uh...

135
00:07:50.011 --> 00:07:53.640
I think even good people can do
bad things if they're pushed.

136
00:07:56.851 --> 00:07:58.728
Sam the man. can you point?

137
00:08:00.230 --> 00:08:02.065
Which one?

138
00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:06.987
Couldn't agree with you more.
Green ones are gross.

139
00:08:07.070 --> 00:08:08.614
Ugh!

140
00:08:08.697 --> 00:08:10.824
Hey. you'll make the
right call on the picture.

141
00:08:10.907 --> 00:08:13.493
'Cause you always
make the right call.

142
00:08:13.576 --> 00:08:15.120
Thank you.

143
00:08:15.203 --> 00:08:16.788
Hey. sweet boy.

144
00:08:16.871 --> 00:08:19.833
Daddy's gonna look
after you today. OK?

145
00:08:19.916 --> 00:08:21.126
You be good for him. OK?

146
00:08:21.209 --> 00:08:24.922
-OK.
-OK. OK.

147
00:08:25.005 --> 00:08:25.964
Let me see.

148
00:08:26.047 --> 00:08:27.299
-Ooh.
-What is that one?

149
00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:29.134
I'm applying
for a new villain loan.

150
00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:31.845
Go by the name of...
both: Vector.

151
00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:36.141
<i>♪ The only one for me is you ♪</i>

152
00:08:36.224 --> 00:08:37.643
♪ And you for me ♪

153
00:08:37.726 --> 00:08:42.814
♪ So happy together ♪

154
00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:47.110
♪ I can't see me
loving nobody but you ♪

155
00:08:47.193 --> 00:08:49.320
♪ For all my life ♪

156
00:08:54.743 --> 00:08:56.286
Hey. Sammy boy. do you
know what a Hail Mary is?

157
00:08:56.369 --> 00:08:57.996
-Yes.
-It's my last big chance. OK?

158
00:08:58.079 --> 00:08:59.081
You ready?
-Yeah.

159
00:08:59.164 --> 00:09:00.832
OK. Ring. ring.

160
00:09:00.915 --> 00:09:03.293
Ring. ring.

161
00:09:08.882 --> 00:09:10.759
Here you go. here you go. Yes.

162
00:09:20.268 --> 00:09:23.104
OK.

163
00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:28.860
Hi.

164
00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:30.195
<i>Hello. Ms. Kaminski.</i>

165
00:09:30.278 --> 00:09:32.864
<i>Thank you for agreeing
to talk to me so early.</i>

166
00:09:32.947 --> 00:09:35.909
Yeah. of course.

167
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:37.202
<i>You and your husband</i>

168
00:09:37.285 --> 00:09:39.037
<i>didn't recognize the man
from the picture.</i>

169
00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:41.123
but. uh. Jacob might.

170
00:09:41.206 --> 00:09:42.791
Uh. you know.
Carrie was his nanny.

171
00:09:42.874 --> 00:09:44.167
<i>and it could be
that he saw Carrie</i>

172
00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:46.003
<i>and that man together
at some point.</i>

173
00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:47.629
<i>Could I get your permission</i>

174
00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:49.256
to show him a picture
and ask him a few questions?

175
00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:50.716
Oh. of course. yeah.

176
00:09:50.799 --> 00:09:52.279
Jacob. can you come
here for a minute?

177
00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:56.805
<i>Come here.</i>

178
00:09:56.888 --> 00:09:58.181
Wait. wait. wait.

179
00:09:58.264 --> 00:09:59.933
<i>This is the man that's
helping to find Milo.</i>

180
00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:02.311
<i>Is it OK if he asks you
a few questions?</i>

181
00:10:02.394 --> 00:10:04.271
<i>Can I show him my letters?</i>

182
00:10:04.354 --> 00:10:06.106
<i>OK. Yeah. but real quick.</i>

183
00:10:06.189 --> 00:10:08.275
<i>He. um. wants to
show you his letters.</i>

184
00:10:08.358 --> 00:10:09.776
<i>He's learning to write.</i>

185
00:10:09.859 --> 00:10:13.113
Oh. yeah. no.
I definitely want to see that.

186
00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:16.074
Ooh. wow.
You are so good. Jacob.

187
00:10:16.157 --> 00:10:17.868
<i>Well done. buddy.</i>

188
00:10:17.951 --> 00:10:19.828
-What do you say?
-Thank you.

189
00:10:19.911 --> 00:10:22.039
No. no. I mean it. Jacob.
You're really good at letters.

190
00:10:22.122 --> 00:10:23.415
Do you have a good memory. too?

191
00:10:23.498 --> 00:10:24.416
<i>Yeah.</i>

192
00:10:24.499 --> 00:10:26.084
Mm. good.

193
00:10:26.167 --> 00:10:27.669
So I'm gonna show you
a picture of a man.

194
00:10:27.752 --> 00:10:29.379
and I want you to tell me
if you recognize him.

195
00:10:29.462 --> 00:10:32.257
<i>OK.</i>

196
00:10:39.514 --> 00:10:42.851
Do you recognize the man
in the picture?

197
00:10:42.934 --> 00:10:44.853
<i>Mm-mm.</i>

198
00:10:45.937 --> 00:10:47.105
It's all right. buddy.

199
00:10:47.188 --> 00:10:48.357
<i>Thank you for looking.</i>

200
00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:50.192
I. uh... I'll keep you updated.
Ms. Kaminski.

201
00:10:50.275 --> 00:10:52.318
<i>Thank you.</i>

202
00:10:58.033 --> 00:10:59.785
You want an airplane?

203
00:10:59.868 --> 00:11:01.703
OK. you ready?

204
00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:05.123
Oh. there's turbulence!

205
00:11:05.206 --> 00:11:06.750
OK. we're back now.

206
00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:08.710
Oh!

207
00:11:26.144 --> 00:11:27.396
Oh. oh. oh. oh. Hey. OK. hey.

208
00:11:27.479 --> 00:11:29.898
I... I need you to be really
quiet for this one. OK?

209
00:11:29.981 --> 00:11:31.817
Ring. ring.

210
00:11:31.900 --> 00:11:32.985
Here.

211
00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:34.486
Go. go. go. go.

212
00:11:37.572 --> 00:11:38.991
Hello. Ms. Irvine.

213
00:11:39.074 --> 00:11:40.993
<i>Oh. hi.</i>

214
00:11:41.076 --> 00:11:45.872
Uh. are there any updates on...

215
00:11:45.955 --> 00:11:47.374
on... on that man?

216
00:11:47.457 --> 00:11:49.167
Uh. no one in
the Kaminski family

217
00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:51.128
recognizes the man. unfortunately.

218
00:11:51.211 --> 00:11:54.339
Uh. I think our next best bet

219
00:11:54.422 --> 00:11:58.218
is to run his picture
in the press.

220
00:12:00.887 --> 00:12:05.267
And. uh. ask the public to
come forward with information.

221
00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:08.312
But. uh.

222
00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:11.106
if he sees his
picture everywhere.

223
00:12:11.189 --> 00:12:12.190
and...

224
00:12:12.273 --> 00:12:15.193
and he has Milo. then...

225
00:12:15.276 --> 00:12:17.154
<i>you know. I...</i>

226
00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:18.488
<i>I think it was different
with... with... with Carrie.</i>

227
00:12:18.571 --> 00:12:20.198
<i>because she's a woman.</i>

228
00:12:20.281 --> 00:12:23.285
and... and we at least know
she took good care of Jacob.

229
00:12:23.368 --> 00:12:26.204
<i>Yeah. no. I understand.</i>

230
00:12:26.287 --> 00:12:28.874
But if this man has Milo

231
00:12:28.957 --> 00:12:33.795
and he sees his face
on the news and...

232
00:12:33.878 --> 00:12:34.878
and panics...

233
00:12:38.133 --> 00:12:39.217
<i>Oh. I'm... I'm... I'm...
I'm sorry.</i>

234
00:12:39.300 --> 00:12:41.302
I'm... I'm...
I'm sorry. Ms. Irvine.

235
00:12:46.349 --> 00:12:49.186
-Uh...
<i>-Stop.</i>

236
00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:52.481
Do... do you think
this is the right thing to do?

237
00:12:52.564 --> 00:12:55.525
Y-yes. I do.

238
00:13:00.488 --> 00:13:02.240
OK.

239
00:13:02.323 --> 00:13:04.451
OK. I. uh. I-I trust you.

240
00:13:04.534 --> 00:13:06.953
<i>Thank you.</i>

241
00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:37.984
And your jacket now.

242
00:13:40.612 --> 00:13:42.406
OK. we'll go in there.
-Now?

243
00:13:42.489 --> 00:13:45.158
Yeah.

244
00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:49.913
Hey.
Hey. can I tell you something?

245
00:13:49.996 --> 00:13:51.290
OK.

246
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:53.250
That you're a good kid
and I love you very much.

247
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:54.376
Yeah!

248
00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:55.919
Now get out of here.

249
00:14:06.638 --> 00:14:09.182
Hey. Hey.

250
00:14:09.265 --> 00:14:11.017
Paul. Honey.

251
00:14:16.398 --> 00:14:18.358
<i>Oh. hey. Rick.
Good to hear from you.</i>

252
00:14:18.441 --> 00:14:20.902
<i>Is this about
the school lottery?</i>

253
00:14:20.985 --> 00:14:22.237
<i>Has Sam gotten in?</i>

254
00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:23.989
<i>No. not exactly.</i>

255
00:14:24.072 --> 00:14:25.407
{\an8}You know I had to step off
the applicant committee.

256
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:26.617
{\an8}<i> Yeah.</i>

257
00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:28.285
{\an8}I know you.
I know Casey and Sam.

258
00:14:28.368 --> 00:14:29.453
{\an8}I-I'd be biased.

259
00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:31.079
{\an8}Of course.

260
00:14:31.162 --> 00:14:32.456
No. no. no. no. it... it...
totally understood.

261
00:14:32.539 --> 00:14:34.917
<i>It was just a joke.
I was just joking.</i>

262
00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:39.087
Look. there's
a lot of applicants this year.

263
00:14:39.170 --> 00:14:41.089
There's only one
reduced tuition spot.

264
00:14:41.172 --> 00:14:43.508
<i>and I know how bad you
and Casey want this for Sam.</i>

265
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:46.053
Yeah. yeah.

266
00:14:46.136 --> 00:14:49.181
I'm just gonna say it.

267
00:14:49.264 --> 00:14:51.266
The associate dean here.

268
00:14:51.349 --> 00:14:53.518
his son was arrested
at a party last night.

269
00:14:53.601 --> 00:14:55.228
<i>Possession of a controlled substance.</i>

270
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:56.563
Xanax?

271
00:14:56.646 --> 00:14:58.065
-How'd you know?
<i>-'Cause he's a rich kid.</i>

272
00:14:58.148 --> 00:14:59.316
<i>They all steal their mom's Xanax</i>

273
00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:00.734
<i>and then they
take it to parties.</i>

274
00:15:00.817 --> 00:15:02.569
Tell him I said he's got
nothing to worry about. OK?

275
00:15:02.652 --> 00:15:05.572
He'll do drug treatment
and community service.

276
00:15:05.655 --> 00:15:07.366
and then he can get it
expunged off his record

277
00:15:07.449 --> 00:15:08.659
if he's clean for a year.

278
00:15:08.742 --> 00:15:11.036
But he's applying
for colleges in the fall.

279
00:15:11.119 --> 00:15:12.037
It won't be expunged by then.

280
00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:13.413
Well. no.

281
00:15:13.496 --> 00:15:14.539
because he got caught
with a controlled substance.

282
00:15:14.622 --> 00:15:16.333
That's how the law works.

283
00:15:16.416 --> 00:15:17.918
<i>Don't you guys. like. have
to prove that it's Xanax?</i>

284
00:15:18.001 --> 00:15:19.378
<i>I saw some documentary
where you...</i>

285
00:15:19.461 --> 00:15:21.171
where you send it away to a lab
to get...

286
00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:23.090
Yeah. send it to the lab
for testing.

287
00:15:23.173 --> 00:15:25.342
We do it for every drug charge.

288
00:15:25.425 --> 00:15:27.010
Has it been sent off yet?

289
00:15:27.093 --> 00:15:28.220
Probably not for a week or two.

290
00:15:28.303 --> 00:15:29.638
Why?

291
00:15:29.721 --> 00:15:31.181
<i>He told the officers
that it was Tylenol.</i>

292
00:15:31.264 --> 00:15:33.642
that he was just carrying it
around in a prescription bottle

293
00:15:33.725 --> 00:15:35.269
to look cool at the party.

294
00:15:35.352 --> 00:15:36.353
<i>But they didn't believe him.</i>

295
00:15:36.436 --> 00:15:38.355
Probably because it wasn't true.

296
00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:45.946
What if it <i>was</i> Tylenol?

297
00:15:46.029 --> 00:15:49.074
I'm not that guy.

298
00:15:49.157 --> 00:15:52.536
It would get Sam
into St. Mark's.

299
00:15:52.619 --> 00:15:55.289
Wait. wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait. wait.

300
00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:58.417
Let me make sure I understand
what's on the table here.

301
00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:02.421
I risk my career to give a rich
kid <i>another</i> advantage in life.

302
00:16:02.504 --> 00:16:04.006
and in exchange.

303
00:16:04.089 --> 00:16:06.258
my kid gets his <i>basic</i>
educational needs met?

304
00:16:06.341 --> 00:16:09.177
<i>And this deal is coming
from a man with the power</i>

305
00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:11.096
<i>to help a dozen kids.
maybe more.</i>

306
00:16:11.179 --> 00:16:13.724
But instead. he offers one spot
to lower-income kids.

307
00:16:13.807 --> 00:16:15.684
One spot.

308
00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:20.063
Fuck it.

309
00:16:20.146 --> 00:16:21.273
Fuck him.

310
00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:23.233
I'm not that guy. pal.

311
00:16:23.316 --> 00:16:24.609
Answer's no.

312
00:17:11.781 --> 00:17:13.367
<i>Breaking news.</i>

313
00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:15.577
<i>The police have released
a photo of a man</i>

314
00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:17.788
<i>they are calling
a person of interest</i>

315
00:17:17.871 --> 00:17:19.498
<i>in the kidnapping...</i>

316
00:17:19.581 --> 00:17:21.583
<i>A new development in the
kidnapping of Milo Irvine.</i>

317
00:17:21.666 --> 00:17:23.252
<i>Police have released a photo</i>

318
00:17:23.335 --> 00:17:26.046
<i>of a person of interest
earlier today.</i>

319
00:17:26.129 --> 00:17:27.589
<i>What this guy
brings out of his...</i>

320
00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:29.424
<i>This guy's face
is everywhere now.</i>

321
00:17:29.507 --> 00:17:32.344
<i>I mean. he can't go anywhere.</i>

322
00:17:32.427 --> 00:17:35.555
<i>If Milo isn't found.
there will be backlash.</i>

323
00:17:35.638 --> 00:17:39.101
<i>To find Milo. it's a good idea.</i>

324
00:17:39.184 --> 00:17:41.186
<i>I mean. if you want
to catch a criminal.</i>

325
00:17:41.269 --> 00:17:43.188
<i>you have to think like them.</i>

326
00:17:43.271 --> 00:17:44.564
<i>We want to find Milo.</i>

327
00:18:12.884 --> 00:18:15.345
Vehicle forensics came
in on the nanny car.

328
00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:16.847
-And?
-There's nothing useful.

329
00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:18.682
There's prints from the dad.
the mom. the kid.

330
00:18:18.765 --> 00:18:20.517
We can identify all of them.

331
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:22.269
There's several prints
from other adults.

332
00:18:22.352 --> 00:18:23.478
just no way to know
which are hers.

333
00:18:23.561 --> 00:18:24.688
So the car was used
by other people?

334
00:18:24.771 --> 00:18:25.856
Yeah. unfortunately.

335
00:18:25.939 --> 00:18:27.357
And it's opened up

336
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:28.692
at this school drive-through.
passenger's side.

337
00:18:28.775 --> 00:18:30.235
by whoever's
getting the kids out.

338
00:18:30.318 --> 00:18:32.446
So there's lots of prints
through the school.

339
00:18:32.529 --> 00:18:33.488
How did we do
at the milkshake shop?

340
00:18:33.571 --> 00:18:35.198
Interviewed four staff members.

341
00:18:35.281 --> 00:18:36.533
Two of them say
they recognized the nannies.

342
00:18:36.616 --> 00:18:38.160
that they stood
in line together.

343
00:18:38.243 --> 00:18:40.287
but they didn't notice
anything else about them.

344
00:18:40.370 --> 00:18:41.413
Said they talked.

345
00:18:41.496 --> 00:18:43.165
Mm.

346
00:18:43.248 --> 00:18:44.458
Anything on our marathon man?

347
00:18:44.541 --> 00:18:45.918
There's a lot of calls.

348
00:18:46.001 --> 00:18:47.794
but nothing that's been flagged
for us yet other than

349
00:18:47.877 --> 00:18:50.213
lots of people still thinking
the whole thing was staged.

350
00:18:50.296 --> 00:18:51.548
Detectives.

351
00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:53.431
think there's someone here
you should talk to.

352
00:19:01.057 --> 00:19:03.185
OK. ma'am. I know
you've spoken to officers

353
00:19:03.268 --> 00:19:04.269
a few different times.

354
00:19:04.352 --> 00:19:05.979
Please allow me to catch up.

355
00:19:06.062 --> 00:19:11.485
So you live
1800 Crescent Hollow Road?

356
00:19:11.568 --> 00:19:12.903
Yes.

357
00:19:12.986 --> 00:19:14.780
The same address that
Marissa Irvine was sent to

358
00:19:14.863 --> 00:19:16.448
the day her child was kidnapped?

359
00:19:16.531 --> 00:19:18.241
Yes.

360
00:19:18.324 --> 00:19:21.745
And now you're saying you
know the man from the marathon?

361
00:19:21.828 --> 00:19:23.705
His name is Kyle Smit.

362
00:19:23.788 --> 00:19:26.583
I was his foster mother
for a little over a year.

363
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:29.795
What got Kyle into
the foster system?

364
00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:32.005
He never had parents
to speak of.

365
00:19:32.088 --> 00:19:34.675
There was an aunt.
but she overdosed.

366
00:19:34.758 --> 00:19:37.427
Oxy. Kyle's from South Shore.

367
00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:39.846
That drug has just destroyed
the whole neighborhood.

368
00:19:39.929 --> 00:19:41.974
Kyle was 16. still a minor.

369
00:19:42.057 --> 00:19:43.600
He was placed with me.

370
00:19:43.683 --> 00:19:45.227
How'd that go?

371
00:19:45.310 --> 00:19:46.853
I loved having him.

372
00:19:46.936 --> 00:19:49.690
And I think he was happy
with me. too.

373
00:19:49.773 --> 00:19:53.360
He enrolled in a GED program.
graduated high school.

374
00:19:53.443 --> 00:19:55.820
I have a picture of that day.

375
00:20:02.077 --> 00:20:04.705
What more can you tell us
about Kyle?

376
00:20:04.788 --> 00:20:07.916
He was a little skittish
by nature.

377
00:20:07.999 --> 00:20:10.043
Otherwise. he was mostly quiet.

378
00:20:10.126 --> 00:20:11.670
And kind.

379
00:20:11.753 --> 00:20:13.922
I don't believe he would
be involved in a kidnapping.

380
00:20:14.005 --> 00:20:15.882
It just doesn't make sense.

381
00:20:15.965 --> 00:20:17.718
Did Kyle have a girlfriend?

382
00:20:17.801 --> 00:20:19.553
Never that I knew of. no.

383
00:20:19.636 --> 00:20:21.638
Do you and Kyle
still keep in touch?

384
00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:25.934
He turned 18 and wasn't
in the foster system anymore.

385
00:20:26.017 --> 00:20:27.352
He went and stayed with a friend

386
00:20:27.435 --> 00:20:29.479
from his old neighborhood
while he looked for work.

387
00:20:29.562 --> 00:20:30.814
And he got a job. too.

388
00:20:30.897 --> 00:20:31.773
Oh. Doing what?

389
00:20:31.856 --> 00:20:32.899
Construction.

390
00:20:32.982 --> 00:20:34.359
Hmm.

391
00:20:34.442 --> 00:20:36.361
And he was so nervous.

392
00:20:36.444 --> 00:20:39.406
He wasn't practical by nature.

393
00:20:39.489 --> 00:20:41.575
He called me on his first day
on his way in.

394
00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:43.285
He had to take a few buses
to get there

395
00:20:43.368 --> 00:20:46.288
and we talked the whole way
till he felt better.

396
00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:47.748
But it doesn't mean anything

397
00:20:47.831 --> 00:20:49.583
at the end of the day. does it?

398
00:20:49.666 --> 00:20:52.836
High school diploma
and a job. sure. but

399
00:20:52.919 --> 00:20:55.422
still can't live off
what they pay you.

400
00:20:55.505 --> 00:20:59.009
Last I heard. he was arrested
for selling OxyContin.

401
00:20:59.092 --> 00:21:01.094
Judge gave him six years.

402
00:21:04.514 --> 00:21:08.560
Ma'am. have you seen
this picture in the news?

403
00:21:08.643 --> 00:21:10.062
Yes.

404
00:21:10.145 --> 00:21:12.606
I know she's suspected of
taking that little boy. Milo.

405
00:21:12.689 --> 00:21:14.107
Do you know her?

406
00:21:14.190 --> 00:21:15.442
No.

407
00:21:15.525 --> 00:21:16.901
Has she ever come to visit Kyle?

408
00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:22.741
No.

409
00:21:22.824 --> 00:21:25.702
Did Kyle ever mention
anyone named Carrie?

410
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:26.954
Caroline?

411
00:21:27.037 --> 00:21:28.997
I'm sorry. no.

412
00:21:30.832 --> 00:21:31.833
OK.

413
00:21:33.043 --> 00:21:34.628
So ma'am. you say

414
00:21:34.711 --> 00:21:35.879
you don't believe Kyle
was involved in the kidnapping.

415
00:21:35.962 --> 00:21:37.631
I don't.

416
00:21:37.714 --> 00:21:38.674
Even though Kyle and
the kidnapper are connected.

417
00:21:38.757 --> 00:21:40.092
we have pictures
of them together.

418
00:21:40.175 --> 00:21:42.803
and you just described Kyle
as a young man

419
00:21:42.886 --> 00:21:45.639
without any money or legitimate
prospects for making money.

420
00:21:45.722 --> 00:21:48.809
And of all addresses
in all of Chicago.

421
00:21:48.892 --> 00:21:51.561
the very wealthy Marissa Irvine
gets sent to your home

422
00:21:51.644 --> 00:21:52.813
on the day of the kidnapping.

423
00:21:52.896 --> 00:21:55.399
the home where Kyle Smit
lived for over a year.

424
00:21:55.482 --> 00:21:59.694
And you honestly believe
that this is all a coincidence?

425
00:22:04.699 --> 00:22:05.826
We have a name.

426
00:22:05.909 --> 00:22:07.953
Kyle Daniel Smit.

427
00:22:08.036 --> 00:22:09.663
The address
Marissa Irvine was texted

428
00:22:09.746 --> 00:22:10.956
on the day of the kidnapping

429
00:22:11.039 --> 00:22:13.083
belongs to Kyle Smit's
former foster mother.

430
00:22:13.166 --> 00:22:14.876
pointing to him as more than
just an acquaintance

431
00:22:14.959 --> 00:22:16.169
of Carrie Finch.

432
00:22:16.252 --> 00:22:17.671
We're now looking
at his potential involvement

433
00:22:17.754 --> 00:22:19.047
in Milo's abduction.

434
00:22:19.130 --> 00:22:20.757
All right. let's pull
everything we can on Kyle.

435
00:22:20.840 --> 00:22:21.883
Let's start with
the driver's license.

436
00:22:21.966 --> 00:22:23.635
I got it here.
State of Illinois.

437
00:22:23.718 --> 00:22:24.720
Expired?

438
00:22:24.803 --> 00:22:26.430
-No. Record's clean.
-OK.

439
00:22:26.513 --> 00:22:28.515
Check in with Hertz
and Enterprise and all of them

440
00:22:28.598 --> 00:22:30.183
and see if
he's rented a car recently.

441
00:22:30.266 --> 00:22:31.852
If so. I want the make. model.
and plate

442
00:22:31.935 --> 00:22:33.437
and any GPS data they have.

443
00:22:33.520 --> 00:22:34.938
After that. credit checks.

444
00:22:35.021 --> 00:22:36.898
How has he spent his money?
Has he rented an apartment?

445
00:22:36.981 --> 00:22:38.859
If he's using an ATM
in the last month.

446
00:22:38.942 --> 00:22:40.986
I want the banking information
and CCTV with it.

447
00:22:41.069 --> 00:22:43.071
We're gonna get pushback
on all those requests.

448
00:22:43.154 --> 00:22:45.157
Unless we're getting a warrant.

449
00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:46.575
Prison file's right here.

450
00:22:46.658 --> 00:22:48.702
What do we need to know?

451
00:22:48.785 --> 00:22:51.622
Uh. drug offense.
like the foster mom said.

452
00:22:51.705 --> 00:22:55.417
Not a single visitor until
a week before his release.

453
00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:59.588
Visitor was Caroline Finch.

454
00:22:59.671 --> 00:23:02.174
OK. Kyle Smit is no longer
a person of interest.

455
00:23:02.257 --> 00:23:03.675
He is now a suspect.

456
00:23:03.758 --> 00:23:04.885
Get that warrant.

457
00:23:04.968 --> 00:23:06.762
I'll get the paperwork
going for the judge.

458
00:23:06.845 --> 00:23:09.473
A prison visit
right before his release.

459
00:23:09.556 --> 00:23:11.683
Carrie's already
working for the Kaminski family

460
00:23:11.766 --> 00:23:13.727
and getting closer
to making her move on Milo.

461
00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:14.978
Let's talk to Kyle's cellmate.

462
00:23:15.061 --> 00:23:17.856
see what he said
after Carrie left that day.

463
00:23:35.123 --> 00:23:37.960
<i>I started my time here
about a year ago.</i>

464
00:23:38.043 --> 00:23:39.628
They put me in with Kyle

465
00:23:39.711 --> 00:23:42.297
and I shared a cell with him
right up until his release.

466
00:23:42.380 --> 00:23:43.882
Did you guys get along?

467
00:23:43.965 --> 00:23:46.593
Yes. sir. Yeah.
I mean. Kyle was quiet.

468
00:23:46.676 --> 00:23:47.970
It wasn't easy
to get to know him.

469
00:23:48.053 --> 00:23:51.598
But. um. he broke down
eventually. started talking.

470
00:23:51.681 --> 00:23:53.558
What did you guys talk about?

471
00:23:53.641 --> 00:23:56.812
Construction. mostly.
We both worked in that.

472
00:23:56.895 --> 00:23:58.981
Kyle was a drywall installer
before he came here.

473
00:23:59.064 --> 00:24:00.148
Is that what you did?

474
00:24:00.231 --> 00:24:01.316
No. sir.

475
00:24:01.399 --> 00:24:02.484
No. I was with. uh.
Secure Builders

476
00:24:02.567 --> 00:24:08.073
up in Crestline there
from 2017 to 2023.

477
00:24:08.156 --> 00:24:09.825
You know. I was a foreman
and I just worked my way up

478
00:24:09.908 --> 00:24:11.201
to project manager.

479
00:24:12.118 --> 00:24:15.872
They're real good people there.

480
00:24:15.955 --> 00:24:16.955
Good people.

481
00:24:19.042 --> 00:24:20.877
Did Kyle ever talk
about a girlfriend?

482
00:24:22.754 --> 00:24:24.256
Most of these guys.
they talk about a girlfriend.

483
00:24:24.339 --> 00:24:25.841
And she is always real pretty.

484
00:24:25.924 --> 00:24:28.718
but never shows up
on visiting day. you know?

485
00:24:30.095 --> 00:24:31.013
Well. did Kyle ever
talk about a girlfriend

486
00:24:31.096 --> 00:24:32.806
that you thought was real?

487
00:24:32.889 --> 00:24:33.889
No.

488
00:24:35.767 --> 00:24:37.060
People like Kyle and me.

489
00:24:37.143 --> 00:24:39.187
we know there's nothing
on the outside anymore.

490
00:24:39.270 --> 00:24:41.106
For us.

491
00:24:41.189 --> 00:24:42.469
it's best not
to talk about that.

492
00:24:44.067 --> 00:24:46.570
Was one girl. though.

493
00:24:46.653 --> 00:24:48.030
She came to visit.

494
00:24:48.113 --> 00:24:50.115
The only reason I remember.
she was the only one.

495
00:24:50.198 --> 00:24:52.200
It was like a week
before he got out.

496
00:24:52.283 --> 00:24:53.952
But I don't know.

497
00:24:54.035 --> 00:24:55.579
He didn't act like it was
his girlfriend or anything.

498
00:24:55.662 --> 00:24:57.789
What did he act like?

499
00:24:57.872 --> 00:24:59.708
He was just...

500
00:24:59.791 --> 00:25:01.084
quiet for a few days.

501
00:25:02.961 --> 00:25:04.630
I thought it was. like.
his sister. cousin.

502
00:25:04.713 --> 00:25:06.006
something like that.

503
00:25:07.048 --> 00:25:08.634
Bad family news.

504
00:25:08.717 --> 00:25:12.596
Uh. you know.
I was just guessing.

505
00:25:12.679 --> 00:25:15.849
Did you see her?
The girl that visited Kyle?

506
00:25:15.932 --> 00:25:18.769
No. sir.

507
00:25:18.852 --> 00:25:20.854
Was it that nanny?

508
00:25:20.937 --> 00:25:22.773
Why do you ask that?

509
00:25:22.856 --> 00:25:25.108
We all seen the news.

510
00:25:25.191 --> 00:25:27.903
Seen the picture.

511
00:25:27.986 --> 00:25:30.072
It's not hard to put
the pieces together.

512
00:25:30.155 --> 00:25:33.075
The woman who visited
Kyle Smit was the nanny. yes.

513
00:25:33.158 --> 00:25:35.118
Carrie Finch.

514
00:25:35.201 --> 00:25:38.372
Though that's not her real name.

515
00:25:38.455 --> 00:25:40.290
All right. pretend you're me

516
00:25:40.373 --> 00:25:43.627
and you want to find Kyle Smit
right now.

517
00:25:43.710 --> 00:25:46.004
Where's the first place
you would look?

518
00:25:46.087 --> 00:25:48.006
Well. usually
I'd say with his dealer.

519
00:25:48.089 --> 00:25:52.886
but. uh. Kyle only sold stuff.
so...

520
00:25:52.969 --> 00:25:54.930
I'd say your best bet's
his old neighborhood.

521
00:25:55.013 --> 00:25:56.098
Nobody there is gonna want
to talk to the cops.

522
00:25:56.181 --> 00:25:58.267
but I'd still try.

523
00:25:58.350 --> 00:26:00.435
Kyle's only relative
from South Shore is long gone.

524
00:26:00.518 --> 00:26:02.396
Do you really think
he'd go back there still?

525
00:26:02.479 --> 00:26:03.939
Seeing his face on TV. you know.

526
00:26:04.022 --> 00:26:06.733
if he knows he's in trouble.

527
00:26:06.816 --> 00:26:09.820
probably just run back
to his old neighborhood.

528
00:26:09.903 --> 00:26:11.363
Might be all he has left.

529
00:26:14.324 --> 00:26:15.825
Hey. thank you.

530
00:26:18.119 --> 00:26:19.829
You're welcome.

531
00:26:24.376 --> 00:26:27.004
You bring that boy home
to his mama.

532
00:26:27.087 --> 00:26:28.755
Yes. sir.

533
00:26:33.343 --> 00:26:36.346
OK. so she visits him
a week before his release.

534
00:26:36.429 --> 00:26:39.224
Doesn't sound like
it was a happy visit.

535
00:26:39.307 --> 00:26:41.977
How do we think they met?

536
00:26:42.060 --> 00:26:44.479
Well. she could have met him
while he was serving time.

537
00:26:44.562 --> 00:26:45.772
What. like through letters?

538
00:26:45.855 --> 00:26:49.276
Yeah. I doubt that. too.

539
00:26:49.359 --> 00:26:51.778
If they knew each other
from before he went in.

540
00:26:51.861 --> 00:26:53.989
it was when Kyle was
living in South Shore.

541
00:26:54.072 --> 00:26:56.908
So it stands to reason
Carrie's from there. too.

542
00:26:56.991 --> 00:26:58.785
Well. officers
found yearbooks from Kyle.

543
00:26:58.868 --> 00:27:00.162
grade school on up.

544
00:27:00.245 --> 00:27:02.914
There's no picture
of anyone who resembles Carrie.

545
00:27:02.997 --> 00:27:04.875
even looking up and down
a few grades.

546
00:27:04.958 --> 00:27:06.919
OK. what was Kyle doing
in South Shore besides school?

547
00:27:07.002 --> 00:27:08.170
Where could he meet somebody?

548
00:27:08.253 --> 00:27:10.172
Work. Construction.

549
00:27:10.255 --> 00:27:11.975
There's not a lot
of young girls in drywall.

550
00:27:14.217 --> 00:27:17.178
That doesn't mean
her dad's not a drywaller.

551
00:27:18.596 --> 00:27:23.185
There's. like. 15 drywall
places in South Shore.

552
00:27:23.268 --> 00:27:25.354
We can send officers out
to all of them now if you want.

553
00:27:25.437 --> 00:27:28.023
I mean. suits are hard enough
in a place like South Shore.

554
00:27:28.106 --> 00:27:29.816
Uniforms are dead in the water.

555
00:27:29.899 --> 00:27:31.401
Let's see
if we can narrow it down.

556
00:27:31.484 --> 00:27:34.071
The aunt who ODed...
what's that address?

557
00:27:34.154 --> 00:27:37.783
That's. uh.
South Bennett Avenue.

558
00:27:37.866 --> 00:27:41.495
OK. The foster mom said when
Kyle turned 18. he left her.

559
00:27:41.578 --> 00:27:42.996
then went back to live
with his old friends.

560
00:27:43.079 --> 00:27:46.124
That's got to be
near South Bennett.

561
00:27:46.207 --> 00:27:47.876
There's. like.
four or five drywalling places

562
00:27:47.959 --> 00:27:49.127
around South Bennett.

563
00:27:49.210 --> 00:27:50.128
Yeah. but we want to look away

564
00:27:50.211 --> 00:27:51.421
from South Bennett. remember?

565
00:27:51.504 --> 00:27:53.048
Because the foster mom
said that Kyle called her

566
00:27:53.131 --> 00:27:54.299
on his commute.

567
00:27:54.382 --> 00:27:55.968
He had a few bus rides.

568
00:27:56.051 --> 00:27:58.220
So if we're starting off
in South Bennett.

569
00:27:58.303 --> 00:28:00.180
what's a drywall place
a few busses out?

570
00:28:00.263 --> 00:28:01.974
Uh...

571
00:28:02.057 --> 00:28:03.058
I got two.

572
00:28:03.141 --> 00:28:05.018
Well. he was arrested in 2019.

573
00:28:05.101 --> 00:28:07.228
Any chance one of them was
around before then?

574
00:28:09.981 --> 00:28:11.900
You got it.

575
00:28:11.983 --> 00:28:14.069
Let's go.

576
00:28:40.679 --> 00:28:43.015
You know. I'm starting
to think people around here

577
00:28:43.098 --> 00:28:44.558
don't like talking to cops.

578
00:28:44.641 --> 00:28:47.019
Yeah. but someone's gonna
want to catch the bus home.

579
00:28:47.102 --> 00:28:49.855
They'll probably be alone and
we could try them again then.

580
00:28:49.938 --> 00:28:51.856
So we'll just wait.

581
00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:56.320
Sam's school call?

582
00:28:56.403 --> 00:28:58.071
No. we're good.

583
00:28:58.154 --> 00:29:00.198
Hey. sorry we're out here
with two cars. you know?

584
00:29:00.281 --> 00:29:01.450
It's no big deal.

585
00:29:01.533 --> 00:29:02.826
It's just if they do call.
you know...

586
00:29:02.909 --> 00:29:03.994
That's how Sam days work. man.

587
00:29:04.077 --> 00:29:07.122
You and Casey trade off.
I get it.

588
00:29:23.555 --> 00:29:25.015
You sleeping?

589
00:29:25.098 --> 00:29:26.433
No. You?

590
00:29:26.516 --> 00:29:28.101
Eh. so-so.

591
00:29:28.184 --> 00:29:30.979
Huh.

592
00:29:38.153 --> 00:29:40.364
I... I saw this thing. and
I can't stop thinking about it.

593
00:29:40.447 --> 00:29:42.991
It's like a...
a loop in my head. you know?

594
00:29:43.074 --> 00:29:45.910
Like OCD. you know?

595
00:29:48.038 --> 00:29:50.999
I saw this documentary
on old sanatoriums.

596
00:29:51.082 --> 00:29:53.252
And back then.

597
00:29:53.335 --> 00:29:55.379
anyone with a mental disorder.
they'd just throw you in.

598
00:29:55.462 --> 00:29:58.214
tie you up. drug you. shock you.

599
00:30:00.300 --> 00:30:03.470
Like. all that stuff.
I already knew. you know?

600
00:30:04.554 --> 00:30:08.100
But then I saw this. uh...

601
00:30:08.183 --> 00:30:10.185
you know. they showed this room

602
00:30:10.268 --> 00:30:12.729
with cribs. but like. big cribs.

603
00:30:15.357 --> 00:30:18.234
For. like.
six- and seven-year-olds.

604
00:30:20.445 --> 00:30:23.073
And the cribs had tops.

605
00:30:26.534 --> 00:30:31.206
And the tops locked. you know.

606
00:30:31.289 --> 00:30:34.084
And that's where they put
the kids who couldn't talk.

607
00:30:37.253 --> 00:30:40.215
Like. that. I. uh...

608
00:30:40.298 --> 00:30:42.467
I didn't know that part.
you know?

609
00:30:52.519 --> 00:30:54.563
Hey. Jim.

610
00:30:54.646 --> 00:30:56.982
Hmm?

611
00:30:57.065 --> 00:30:59.693
Sam's a happy kid.

612
00:30:59.776 --> 00:31:03.738
Every time I see him.
he's smiling.

613
00:31:05.490 --> 00:31:06.491
Yeah. he likes you.

614
00:31:06.574 --> 00:31:09.286
It's 'cause I bring him candy.

615
00:31:09.369 --> 00:31:12.122
I'm not above bribery.

616
00:31:19.629 --> 00:31:21.589
Here we go.

617
00:31:24.551 --> 00:31:26.762
Ma'am. sorry to bother you.

618
00:31:26.845 --> 00:31:28.430
We didn't get a chance
to talk to you inside.

619
00:31:28.513 --> 00:31:30.057
-Yeah. we're not talking now.
-You were on the phone.

620
00:31:30.140 --> 00:31:32.351
Go away.

621
00:31:32.434 --> 00:31:33.602
It's about a missing child.

622
00:31:33.685 --> 00:31:35.270
I don't know anything.

623
00:31:35.353 --> 00:31:36.271
Was there ever an employee

624
00:31:36.354 --> 00:31:38.982
named Kyle Smit
working with you?

625
00:31:39.065 --> 00:31:40.442
Did you have any interaction
with him at all?

626
00:31:40.525 --> 00:31:43.445
Anything you can tell us?

627
00:31:43.528 --> 00:31:45.405
You recognize her at all?

628
00:31:45.488 --> 00:31:47.240
Maybe seen her around?

629
00:31:47.323 --> 00:31:48.742
She goes by the name
Carrie Finch.

630
00:31:52.787 --> 00:31:55.415
Never seen her.

631
00:32:02.380 --> 00:32:04.633
Yeah.

632
00:32:04.716 --> 00:32:08.095
OK. get a BOLO out now and send
me the last known coordinates

633
00:32:08.178 --> 00:32:11.473
and a list of all the hotels
and motels in the area.

634
00:32:11.556 --> 00:32:14.184
Abandoned houses. too. Good man.

635
00:32:16.561 --> 00:32:21.066
Kyle Smit rented a 2019
white Toyota Camry a week ago.

636
00:32:21.149 --> 00:32:22.401
Hasn't returned it.

637
00:32:22.484 --> 00:32:24.653
GPS was disabled.

638
00:32:24.736 --> 00:32:26.696
We got our car.

639
00:32:38.750 --> 00:32:41.628
Carrie Finch.

640
00:32:41.711 --> 00:32:44.589
Where'd you come up
with that name. Josie?

641
00:32:50.762 --> 00:32:52.097
Peter will be back soon.

642
00:32:52.180 --> 00:32:54.307
He's putting up some flyers
with his sister.

643
00:32:58.228 --> 00:33:01.732
One of us always stays
at the house in case.

644
00:33:01.815 --> 00:33:03.775
Uh. you know.

645
00:33:03.858 --> 00:33:06.528
It's funny how fast
you set up patterns.

646
00:33:06.611 --> 00:33:07.654
Yeah.

647
00:33:12.242 --> 00:33:15.245
Milo was really creative
with his colors.

648
00:33:15.328 --> 00:33:17.164
Yeah.

649
00:33:17.247 --> 00:33:18.624
Yeah. he wouldn't...

650
00:33:18.707 --> 00:33:20.208
He wouldn't
practice the alphabet

651
00:33:20.291 --> 00:33:21.668
unless we got him new markers.

652
00:33:21.751 --> 00:33:22.751
Mm-hmm.

653
00:33:30.927 --> 00:33:32.762
His name is Kyle Smit.

654
00:33:34.764 --> 00:33:38.143
Is that name familiar
to you at all?

655
00:33:38.226 --> 00:33:39.603
That name?

656
00:33:39.686 --> 00:33:41.605
-No.
-No?

657
00:33:41.688 --> 00:33:43.607
He was. uh. recently
released from prison

658
00:33:43.690 --> 00:33:45.776
for a nonviolent offense.

659
00:33:45.859 --> 00:33:48.820
Carrie visited Kyle
a week before he was released.

660
00:33:48.903 --> 00:33:52.240
and that connects them
even before the marathon.

661
00:33:52.323 --> 00:33:54.952
Uh...

662
00:33:55.035 --> 00:33:57.537
what was he in... in prison for?

663
00:33:57.620 --> 00:33:59.331
Possession with intent to sell.

664
00:33:59.414 --> 00:34:02.751
A Schedule II substance.
Uh. OxyContin.

665
00:34:04.586 --> 00:34:07.256
So we now have two adults
working in tandem

666
00:34:07.339 --> 00:34:10.550
to carry out a very complex
and risky crime.

667
00:34:10.633 --> 00:34:12.511
two adults that would have
to be on the same page

668
00:34:12.594 --> 00:34:16.556
about their motivation
to kidnap a very young child.

669
00:34:16.639 --> 00:34:18.308
It doesn't appear
as though either of you

670
00:34:18.391 --> 00:34:21.687
have a personal connection
with Kyle or Carrie.

671
00:34:21.770 --> 00:34:23.855
which means that
it's highly likely

672
00:34:23.938 --> 00:34:27.233
that the motivation
behind the crime is financial.

673
00:34:28.735 --> 00:34:31.947
Now. it can be a temptation
to handle a ransom demand

674
00:34:32.030 --> 00:34:33.657
without coordinating
with the police.

675
00:34:33.740 --> 00:34:38.495
but please believe me. that is
not the right course of action.

676
00:34:38.578 --> 00:34:41.956
But we're not handling
anything on our own.

677
00:34:53.468 --> 00:34:56.555
What's your son's name?

678
00:34:56.638 --> 00:34:58.849
Sam.

679
00:34:58.932 --> 00:35:00.350
I'm sorry.

680
00:35:00.433 --> 00:35:01.435
I-I didn't mean for you
to hear him like that.

681
00:35:01.518 --> 00:35:04.354
Oh. it's OK. It's all right.

682
00:35:04.437 --> 00:35:07.899
How old is he?

683
00:35:07.982 --> 00:35:09.984
He's 13.

684
00:35:12.362 --> 00:35:14.656
He's got a few disabilities.

685
00:35:14.739 --> 00:35:19.411
You know. he can't speak
or understand very much.

686
00:35:19.494 --> 00:35:21.413
Do you have a picture?

687
00:35:23.957 --> 00:35:25.042
Uh. you don't have to show me.

688
00:35:25.125 --> 00:35:26.376
No. no. it's...
it's... it's fine.

689
00:35:26.459 --> 00:35:27.585
It's fine.

690
00:35:30.839 --> 00:35:33.425
Oh. he's cute.

691
00:35:33.508 --> 00:35:35.510
Thank you.

692
00:35:35.593 --> 00:35:36.928
He looks happy.

693
00:35:41.474 --> 00:35:43.518
You want to sit down?

694
00:35:43.601 --> 00:35:44.601
Yeah.

695
00:35:53.611 --> 00:35:56.698
Do you worry about him?

696
00:35:56.781 --> 00:35:58.325
Everyone worries
about their kids. right?

697
00:35:58.408 --> 00:36:01.619
I mean. I haven't cornered
the market on that one.

698
00:36:04.497 --> 00:36:06.624
Well. that's not how you feel.

699
00:36:08.501 --> 00:36:10.462
Well. it's not.

700
00:36:10.545 --> 00:36:11.922
You don't have to tell me
how you do feel.

701
00:36:12.005 --> 00:36:13.590
It's none of my business.

702
00:36:13.673 --> 00:36:16.885
But I know a rehearsed answer
when I hear one.

703
00:36:19.804 --> 00:36:21.389
You do worry.

704
00:36:23.183 --> 00:36:24.934
More than most.

705
00:36:28.688 --> 00:36:31.942
Um...

706
00:36:32.025 --> 00:36:33.986
Mrs. Irvine. is...

707
00:36:34.069 --> 00:36:35.862
is there a chance that
your husband may have

708
00:36:35.945 --> 00:36:40.826
received a ransom notification
and perhaps not told you?

709
00:36:40.909 --> 00:36:42.786
No. no.

710
00:36:42.869 --> 00:36:44.037
He wouldn't do that.

711
00:36:44.120 --> 00:36:45.914
He wouldn't keep something
that big from me.

712
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:52.629
He likes to take care of people
and. uh...

713
00:36:52.712 --> 00:36:56.842
You know.
takes charge on instinct a lot.

714
00:36:56.925 --> 00:37:00.762
But no. not... not that.

715
00:37:00.845 --> 00:37:03.056
Not with this.

716
00:37:03.139 --> 00:37:06.893
Why do you think he likes
to take care of people so much?

717
00:37:08.937 --> 00:37:11.481
Uh. I don't know.

718
00:37:11.564 --> 00:37:14.443
I think he's just
always done it.

719
00:37:14.526 --> 00:37:16.570
He's always been in charge
of his siblings.

720
00:37:16.653 --> 00:37:19.406
Yeah. Peter said there was an
accident when they were kids.

721
00:37:19.489 --> 00:37:23.869
Mm. yeah. He was ten.

722
00:37:23.952 --> 00:37:25.787
Yeah.

723
00:37:25.870 --> 00:37:28.957
Uh. Lia and Brian.
they were little.

724
00:37:29.040 --> 00:37:31.835
Four and six. I think.

725
00:37:31.918 --> 00:37:35.505
You know. they were playing and
she was overexcited and hyper

726
00:37:35.588 --> 00:37:36.923
and Brian...

727
00:37:41.261 --> 00:37:45.682
It was an accident. how he fell.

728
00:37:45.765 --> 00:37:51.438
But I think that it's...

729
00:37:51.521 --> 00:37:54.524
Lia has grown up with that
on her conscience.

730
00:37:54.607 --> 00:37:58.820
And it's sort of shaped
who she is as a person.

731
00:38:01.740 --> 00:38:03.909
I don't know.

732
00:38:03.992 --> 00:38:05.535
We all have our own shit.
though. hey?

733
00:38:14.627 --> 00:38:19.424
I worry about Sam getting sick.

734
00:38:19.507 --> 00:38:21.092
Like cancer.

735
00:38:23.219 --> 00:38:27.933
You know. he's having symptoms
and he can't tell us.

736
00:38:28.016 --> 00:38:30.643
so we don't catch it
until it's too late.

737
00:38:33.313 --> 00:38:38.068
I worry about when my wife
and I are gone and

738
00:38:38.151 --> 00:38:42.030
Sam getting older in some
crappy public-funded home.

739
00:38:42.113 --> 00:38:44.908
I worry about who's
gonna take care of him.

740
00:38:44.991 --> 00:38:48.078
Are they gonna be nice to him?

741
00:38:48.161 --> 00:38:50.956
And lately...

742
00:38:51.039 --> 00:38:53.166
lately. I worry. uh...

743
00:38:57.671 --> 00:39:01.550
That maybe I'm sort of happy

744
00:39:01.633 --> 00:39:05.095
that he doesn't understand

745
00:39:05.178 --> 00:39:10.100
so much. you know. because if...
because if he did...

746
00:39:10.183 --> 00:39:14.104
if he knew me better. then maybe

747
00:39:14.187 --> 00:39:16.898
he wouldn't hug me
the way he does. you know?

748
00:39:23.363 --> 00:39:27.659
That's...
that's what I think of.

749
00:39:33.248 --> 00:39:39.087
I promised myself that. uh...

750
00:39:39.170 --> 00:39:43.592
if Milo comes...

751
00:39:43.675 --> 00:39:48.221
uh. when Milo comes back.

752
00:39:48.304 --> 00:39:52.225
I will do whatever it takes

753
00:39:52.308 --> 00:39:56.813
to make sure that nothing bad
ever happens to him again.

754
00:39:58.314 --> 00:40:01.818
Doesn't matter
what it is. I will do it.

755
00:40:04.612 --> 00:40:07.115
Because that's our job.

756
00:40:07.198 --> 00:40:10.869
We'd do anything for our kids.

757
00:40:10.952 --> 00:40:12.579
Anything.

758
00:40:21.212 --> 00:40:23.131
The address you were given
for Milo's playdate.

759
00:40:23.214 --> 00:40:24.800
1800 Crescent Hollow Road?

760
00:40:24.883 --> 00:40:26.634
Yeah.

761
00:40:27.927 --> 00:40:29.263
The woman who lives there...

762
00:40:29.346 --> 00:40:32.099
-Esther.
-Esther.

763
00:40:32.182 --> 00:40:35.894
She was Kyle Smit's foster mom.

764
00:40:35.977 --> 00:40:38.272
What?

765
00:40:38.355 --> 00:40:42.859
Uh. well. I... well.
I have to talk to her. then.

766
00:40:44.778 --> 00:40:46.237
One thing.

767
00:40:47.906 --> 00:40:51.118
Esther was the only person
in Kyle's life

768
00:40:51.201 --> 00:40:52.285
to ever be kind to him.

769
00:40:54.329 --> 00:40:58.667
And if Kyle is involved
in your son's kidnapping.

770
00:40:58.750 --> 00:41:01.753
he knew you were gonna have
the worst day of your life.

771
00:41:01.836 --> 00:41:04.631
and he sent you to the
most loving person he knew.

772
00:41:08.134 --> 00:41:10.887
That's not nothing.

773
00:41:23.817 --> 00:41:25.444
-Hey. Jackson.
-Hey.

774
00:41:25.527 --> 00:41:26.695
Hey.

775
00:41:28.113 --> 00:41:31.658
Sam was such
a blessing today. really.

776
00:41:31.741 --> 00:41:34.077
Oh. I'm glad to hear that.

777
00:41:34.160 --> 00:41:36.079
We've been short-staffed all day

778
00:41:36.162 --> 00:41:38.040
and a few of the other kids
were struggling a bit.

779
00:41:38.123 --> 00:41:40.918
I was sure I was going to have
to call you or your wife.

780
00:41:41.001 --> 00:41:43.712
But then Sam.
he came through for us.

781
00:41:43.795 --> 00:41:44.838
Sam the man.

782
00:41:44.921 --> 00:41:46.131
He's been over there
doing his puzzle

783
00:41:46.214 --> 00:41:47.966
for the last two hours.

784
00:41:48.049 --> 00:41:50.010
Two hours? Wow.

785
00:41:50.093 --> 00:41:51.261
He is a sweet boy.

786
00:41:51.344 --> 00:41:52.971
I love having him here with us.

787
00:41:53.054 --> 00:41:54.431
Thank you. thank you.

788
00:41:54.514 --> 00:41:57.726
Sam the man.

789
00:41:57.809 --> 00:41:59.478
Hey. I heard you were
pretty great today.

790
00:41:59.561 --> 00:42:00.729
Right.

791
00:42:00.812 --> 00:42:02.689
Can I get a hug?

792
00:42:02.772 --> 00:42:04.816
Oh!

793
00:42:08.528 --> 00:42:10.113
One more hug. One more hug.

794
00:42:13.158 --> 00:42:17.287
Yeah.

795
00:42:51.112 --> 00:42:52.155
Here.

796
00:42:54.449 --> 00:42:56.493
You know the deal. OK?

797
00:42:56.576 --> 00:42:57.953
-No Mommy.
-Don't tell Mommy.

798
00:42:58.036 --> 00:43:00.956
Yeah. It's nice.

799
00:43:01.039 --> 00:43:03.083
Nice.

800
00:43:09.130 --> 00:43:10.256
Like that.

801
00:43:19.349 --> 00:43:21.434
Thank you. Sammy.

802
00:43:55.343 --> 00:44:00.849
Oh. are you?

803
00:44:00.932 --> 00:44:02.225
-How is it?
-Good.

804
00:44:02.308 --> 00:44:03.351
Good?

805
00:44:08.898 --> 00:44:10.233
OK. spit.

806
00:44:11.526 --> 00:44:12.986
Now get out of here.

807
00:45:59.342 --> 00:46:00.344
Yeah?

808
00:46:00.427 --> 00:46:01.720
<i>You made the right call</i>

809
00:46:01.803 --> 00:46:03.388
<i>releasing the picture
of that marathon man.</i>

810
00:46:03.471 --> 00:46:04.681
<i>First we got his name.</i>

811
00:46:04.764 --> 00:46:06.266
<i>now we've got
our biggest lead yet.</i>

812
00:46:06.349 --> 00:46:07.642
On my way.

813
00:46:26.703 --> 00:46:27.746
So I wasn't sure if it was him

814
00:46:27.829 --> 00:46:29.247
from the picture on the news.

815
00:46:29.330 --> 00:46:32.459
but when you said what kind of
car you were looking for.

816
00:46:32.542 --> 00:46:35.211
I went back
and checked out cameras.

817
00:46:37.464 --> 00:46:39.466
That the guy you want?

818
00:46:41.843 --> 00:46:43.220
It is.

819
00:46:43.303 --> 00:46:45.639
Did he come inside
to pay for anything?

820
00:46:45.722 --> 00:46:47.766
Yeah. but we don't
have those tapes.

821
00:46:47.849 --> 00:46:49.685
Rerecorded today. sorry.

822
00:46:49.768 --> 00:46:51.270
What can you tell us about him?

823
00:46:51.353 --> 00:46:54.481
Just that he bought
some mac and cheese.

824
00:46:54.564 --> 00:46:56.149
Anything else?

825
00:46:56.232 --> 00:46:57.317
No.

826
00:46:57.400 --> 00:46:59.319
We're gonna need a copy of that.

827
00:46:59.402 --> 00:47:00.821
What kind of mac and cheese?

828
00:47:00.904 --> 00:47:02.656
Huh?

829
00:47:02.739 --> 00:47:04.241
Well. there's the kind
that you make in a microwave

830
00:47:04.324 --> 00:47:06.326
and the other. you need a stove.

831
00:47:08.912 --> 00:47:12.040
Which one did he buy?

832
00:47:12.123 --> 00:47:15.043
A lot of shitty hotels
and motels have microwaves

833
00:47:15.126 --> 00:47:16.628
either in the room
or at the front desk.

834
00:47:16.711 --> 00:47:18.422
but none of them have stoves.

835
00:47:18.505 --> 00:47:21.717
Kyle Smit bought mac and cheese
that had to be made on a stove.

836
00:47:21.800 --> 00:47:24.595
They gotta have a house
around here somewhere.

837
00:47:24.678 --> 00:47:27.472
Yeah. and it'd have to
be somewhere close to here.

838
00:47:27.555 --> 00:47:29.349
They wouldn't risk
driving a long distance.

839
00:47:29.432 --> 00:47:30.725
not just for some food.

840
00:47:33.311 --> 00:47:35.751
There's a bunch of little lake
house rentals right over there.

841
00:47:38.775 --> 00:47:42.195
This is the closest place
to buy groceries.

842
00:47:46.866 --> 00:47:48.285
Well. I mean. sure.

843
00:47:48.368 --> 00:47:49.870
she's just about the same age
as the kidnapper.

844
00:47:49.953 --> 00:47:53.540
But they don't look alike.
I don't think.

845
00:47:53.623 --> 00:47:58.378
Her hair was darker and long.
and...

846
00:47:58.461 --> 00:48:01.506
yeah. she was all done up
in makeup.

847
00:48:01.589 --> 00:48:03.216
Is this her place?

848
00:48:03.299 --> 00:48:04.635
Yeah.

849
00:48:04.718 --> 00:48:06.845
I mean. I'll show if you like.

850
00:48:06.928 --> 00:48:09.181
-Mm.
-But she's gone for sure.

851
00:48:09.264 --> 00:48:10.474
So she checked out?

852
00:48:10.557 --> 00:48:12.642
She didn't have to.
She paid in advance.

853
00:48:18.189 --> 00:48:19.691
It's just in here.

854
00:48:42.714 --> 00:48:44.424
<i>Granny?</i>

855
00:48:44.507 --> 00:48:46.885
<i>Granny must be having a party.</i>

856
00:48:46.968 --> 00:48:50.847
<i>I hope they are careful
with their cigarettes.</i>

857
00:48:54.351 --> 00:48:55.935
<i>Here it comes.</i>

858
00:49:04.986 --> 00:49:08.156
<i>All: Granny!
-Come in!</i>

859
00:49:08.239 --> 00:49:09.574
<i>Hi. Granny!</i>

860
00:49:22.962 --> 00:49:25.340
Call forensics.

861
00:50:02.752 --> 00:50:04.504
Hey. honey.
Sorry. this is taking a while.

862
00:50:04.587 --> 00:50:06.506
I. uh...
<i>-Have you checked your email?</i>

863
00:50:06.589 --> 00:50:08.258
<i>Honey?</i>
-No. no.

864
00:50:08.341 --> 00:50:10.302
<i>H-he got in.</i>

865
00:50:10.385 --> 00:50:12.387
<i>Sam's got into St. Mark's.</i>

866
00:50:12.470 --> 00:50:13.847
-Oh. really?
<i>-Really!</i>

867
00:50:13.930 --> 00:50:15.265
<i>It's happened.</i>

868
00:50:15.348 --> 00:50:16.892
<i>I don't know how it happened.</i>

869
00:50:16.975 --> 00:50:18.352
<i>but it's happened.
and I can't...</i>

870
00:50:18.435 --> 00:50:19.519
<i>I can't even.</i>

871
00:50:19.602 --> 00:50:21.521
<i>I'm so happy!</i>

872
00:50:21.604 --> 00:50:23.398
<i>I feel so guilty.</i>

873
00:50:23.481 --> 00:50:26.026
<i>All those other parents
will be devastated.</i>

874
00:50:26.109 --> 00:50:27.909
<i>I mean. these are...
these are people we know.</i>

875
00:50:32.365 --> 00:50:35.702
<i>Everybody deserves it
just as much as our Sam.</i>

876
00:50:35.785 --> 00:50:37.579
<i>Oh. God. I feel horrible.</i>

877
00:50:37.662 --> 00:50:39.373
But I'm so relieved.

878
00:50:39.456 --> 00:50:41.249
We found a body.

879
00:50:41.332 --> 00:50:44.711
<i>We're just the luckiest people.</i>

880
00:50:44.794 --> 00:50:48.298
Honey. uh. I'll call you back.
